  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "Kid Kool and the Quest for the Seven Wonder Herbs is a 1988 video game by Vic Tokai for the Nintendo Entertainment System. The game's main character is based on a popular Japanese child actor Kenji Sagara, known for his impersonation of baseball player Masayuki Kakefu.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    },
    {
      "text": "『Kid Kool and the Quest for the Seven Wonder Herbs』は、ヴィック・トカイが任天堂のファミコン向けに制作した1988年のビデオゲームです。このゲームの主人公は、野球選手のかけふ正之のモノマネで知られる人気の子役、相良健二をモデルにしています。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "ai_local_gemma4",
